Location of the city of Superior in Douglas County, Wisconsin |website = |footnotes = }} Superior is a city in northwestern Wisconsin, United States. At the 2020 census, the population was 26,751. Superior is at the western end of Lake Superior. It is also the county seat of Douglas County. Superior was the last place that the Edmund Fitzgerald visited before it sank. ==References== Category:Cities in Wisconsin Category:County seats in Wisconsin
